The SGX S&P CNX Nifty Index futures
for March delivery rose 0.7 percent to 5,380 at 11:01 a.m. in  Singapore .  The futures, derived from the 50 stocks on the underlying
S&P CNX Nifty Index on the National Stock Exchange of India Ltd.,
yesterday rose 0.3 percent to 5,343 at the close in Singapore,
and advanced 0.5 percent to 5,338.00 in Mumbai.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
